WEBVTT

00:08.700 --> 00:12.120
Hi there! Welcome to
this video where we

00:12.120 --> 00:13.540
are going to learn
about digital

00:13.540 --> 00:17.380
identity. In today's
digital world, we all

00:17.380 --> 00:19.860
use devices connected
to the internet and

00:19.860 --> 00:22.220
these devices help
systems recognize who

00:22.220 --> 00:25.640
we are. Let's explore
what digital identity

00:25.640 --> 00:28.060
means and why it is
important to protect

00:28.060 --> 00:31.460
it. The goal of this
video is to help you

00:31.460 --> 00:33.620
understand what
digital identity is

00:33.620 --> 00:37.320
and why it matters.
First, we will look

00:37.320 --> 00:39.020
at what identity
means in everyday

00:39.020 --> 00:41.940
life. Then, we will
explore how identity

00:41.940 --> 00:45.860
works online. Finally
, we will explain why

00:45.860 --> 00:47.680
protecting your
digital identity is

00:47.680 --> 00:48.400
important.

00:53.080 --> 00:55.680
Every person has an
identity in real life

00:56.860 --> 00:58.880
Your identity
includes things like

00:58.880 --> 01:01.540
your name, your face,
your voice, and how

01:01.540 --> 01:04.360
other people
recognize you. These

01:04.360 --> 01:06.380
things help people
know who you are at

01:06.380 --> 01:09.180
school, at home, and
in your community.

01:09.180 --> 01:11.780
When we use digital
devices connected to

01:11.780 --> 01:13.900
the internet, we also
have an identity

01:13.900 --> 01:16.400
online. This is
called a digital

01:16.400 --> 01:19.680
identity. Just like
in real life, your

01:19.680 --> 01:21.520
digital identity
helps systems and

01:21.520 --> 01:23.360
people recognize you
online.

01:27.500 --> 01:29.940
Your digital identity
is created when you

01:29.940 --> 01:32.720
use online services,
apps, games, or

01:32.720 --> 01:35.640
school platforms.
Each time you log in

01:35.640 --> 01:37.920
or create an account,
part of your digital

01:37.920 --> 01:41.520
identity is used.
Usernames are one

01:41.520 --> 01:43.920
part of your digital
identity. They are

01:43.920 --> 01:45.700
often the name that
systems use to

01:45.700 --> 01:48.840
recognize you. Some
people use their real

01:48.840 --> 01:51.080
name, while others
use nicknames or made

01:51.080 --> 01:54.140
-up names. Profile
pictures are another

01:54.140 --> 01:56.720
part of digital
identity. These

01:56.720 --> 01:59.060
images help others
recognize you online,

01:59.060 --> 02:03.000
just like a photo on
an ID card. In games

02:03.000 --> 02:05.420
and virtual worlds,
people often use

02:05.420 --> 02:08.660
avatars. An avatar is
a character or image

02:08.660 --> 02:10.800
that represents you.
Even if it looks

02:10.800 --> 02:12.800
different from you,
it is still part of

02:12.800 --> 02:16.300
your digital identity
. School accounts are

02:16.300 --> 02:18.300
an important part of
your digital identity

02:18.300 --> 02:20.320
. They allow you to
access learning

02:20.320 --> 02:22.540
platforms, homework,
and communication

02:22.540 --> 02:23.860
tools.

02:28.100 --> 02:30.500
Your digital identity
is connected to your

02:30.500 --> 02:33.280
digital assets.
Digital assets are

02:33.280 --> 02:35.600
things that belong to
you online, such as

02:35.600 --> 02:38.700
photos, messages, and
schoolwork. If

02:38.700 --> 02:40.440
someone gets access
to your digital

02:40.440 --> 02:42.900
identity, they may
also get access to

02:42.900 --> 02:45.400
your digital assets.
That is why

02:45.400 --> 02:47.320
protecting your
digital identity is

02:47.320 --> 02:49.460
so important.
Protecting your

02:49.460 --> 02:51.040
digital identity
helps keep your

02:51.040 --> 02:53.700
information private
and safe. It also

02:53.700 --> 02:55.100
helps prevent other
people from

02:55.100 --> 02:58.040
pretending to be you
online. In the next

02:58.040 --> 02:59.580
videos, you will
learn about

02:59.580 --> 03:01.780
authentication and
passwords, which are

03:01.780 --> 03:03.580
tools that help
protect your digital

03:03.580 --> 03:05.640
identity.
Understanding your

03:05.640 --> 03:08.040
digital identity is
the first step to

03:08.040 --> 03:09.900
staying safe online
and making

03:09.900 --> 03:11.760
responsible choices
in digital

03:11.760 --> 03:15.380
environments. So in
this video, we

03:15.380 --> 03:17.820
learned what digital
identity is and why

03:17.820 --> 03:21.700
it matters. Next,
watch the video on

03:21.700 --> 03:23.860
authentication to
learn how systems

03:23.860 --> 03:26.740
check who you are
online.

03:26.740 --> 03:26.880
Thank you for watching.